                  <persName><ref target="/persons/pers1353.xml"/>John Manners</persName> and joined
                  the Methodists in <date when="1761">1761</date>. He received episcopal ordination
                  and by early <date when="1762">1762</date> was assisting <persName><ref
                        target="/persons/pers2180.xml"/>JW</persName> as a clergyman in the
                     <placeName>London</placeName> chapels. He was briefly drawn in with the
                  &apos;enthusiasm&apos; of <persName><ref target="/persons/pers0134.xml"/>eorge
                     Bell</persName> and <persName><ref target="/persons/pers1404.xml"/>Thomas
                     Maxfield</persName>, but reclaimed by <persName><ref
                        target="/persons/pers1353.xml"/>Manners</persName> and appointed to
                     <placeName>Newcastle upon Tyne</placeName> in <date when="1763">1763</date>. By
                     <date when="1767">1767</date> he was back in <placeName>London</placeName>,
                  where he married <persName>Elizabeth La Croissette</persName> in <date
                     when="1767-06">June</date>, but passed away by the end of the year. See Atmore,
